defaultIn a scientific context, uncertainty is the correct concept.  In terms of making decisions, either in politics or business, the concept of risk is potentially far more useful.  
defaultIn informing policy and the public, scientists working in this area should be a
defaults objective as they possibly can about the level of risk where there is uncertainty or less than full understanding. 
defaultRisks to human society and the biosphere are expected to be covered in t
defaulthe IPCC Working Group II Report
default.
defaultThe IPCC AR5 WG1 dedicates one whole chapter of its report (Chapter 9) to the evaluation of climate models.  
defaultThe summary to this chapter gives a fair assessment of the improvements made by climate modellers since the last Assessment r
defaulteport (AR4) as well as the remaining challenges.  For example, t
defaulthe AR5 
defaultWG1 TS 
defaultsuggests that some models may be too responsive to the effects of greenhouse gases.  
