defaultWe agree however, with the key conclusion of the authors of Chapter 9 that
default,
default “
defaultClimate and Earth System models are based on physical principles, and they reproduce many important aspects
default of observed climate. Both aspects contribute to our confidence in the models’ suitability for their application in detection and attribution studies (Chapter 10) and for quantitative future predictions and projections.
default”
defaultThis does not imply bind acceptance
default of the results from the current models: continual questioning of the results and improvements in the models is crucial.
